#Power Transformation (Box-Cox & Yeo-Johnson)

📊 Power Transformation (Box-Cox & Yeo-Johnson)


🔹 What is Power Transformation?

Power Transformation is used to make data more normally distributed.

Many machine learning algorithms perform better when:

Data is normally distributed
Variance is stable
Skewness is reduced
🔹 Types of Power Transformation
1️⃣ Box-Cox Transformation
Works only with positive values
Used to reduce right skewness
Common in statistical modeling
2️⃣ Yeo-Johnson Transformation
Works with positive and negative values
More flexible than Box-Cox
Useful in real-world datasets
🔹 Why Do We Use Power Transformation?

In real datasets:

Features are often skewed
Data may not follow normal distribution
Models may perform poorly

Power transformation helps:

✔ Reduce skewness
✔ Stabilize variance
✔ Improve model accuracy
✔ Meet model assumptions

🔹 When to Use
When data is highly skewed
When using statistical models
Before applying linear models
During feature preprocessing
